---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import CTABand from "../components/CTABand.astro";
---

<Base
  title="Services & pricing"
  description="Flat-rate website builds at about half typical agency pricing, plus a $45/month care plan with hosting included — for Springfield-area small businesses."
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="kicker">Services</p>
      <h1>About half what an agency quotes. Flat. In writing.</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        Around here a professionally built small-business site runs $2,000–$6,000,
        then $50–195 every month for "maintenance." Those quotes carry a lot of
        overhead. Mine carry one engineer — so I charge about half and still put
        more actual work into your site.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section tight">
    <h2 class="sr-only">Packages</h2>
    <div class="wrap grid grid-3">
      <div class="card price">
        <h3>Starter site</h3>
        <p class="band">$1,200 <span>flat</span></p>
        <p class="compare">Typical agency: $2,000–2,500</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Up to 5 pages, mobile-first</li>
          <li>Contact form that lands in your email</li>
          <li>Google Business Profile setup</li>
          <li>Structured data for local search</li>
          <li>Automated tests run before every update</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="fit">For: a business that needs a real web presence this month.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card price featured">
        <h3>Business site</h3>
        <p class="band">$2,900 <span>flat</span></p>
        <p class="compare">Typical agency: $5,000–6,000+</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Everything in Starter, plus:</li>
          <li>Up to 15 pages</li>
          <li>Per-city landing pages for local SEO</li>
          <li>Reviews section, photo gallery</li>
          <li>Full automated test suite in CI</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="fit">For: contractors and services competing across the metro.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card price">
        <h3>Site rescue</h3>
        <p class="band">$1,900 <span>flat</span></p>
        <p class="compare">Typical rebuild quote: $4,000+</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Full rebuild, up to 15 pages, reusing your existing content</li>
          <li>Escape page-builder monthly fees</li>
          <li>Speed and defect audit included</li>
          <li>URLs preserved, redirects mapped to protect your rankings</li>
          <li>Same automated test suite as a new build</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="fit">
          For: anyone paying rent on a site they don't control. It costs less
          than a Business build because your words and photos already exist —
          the rebuild skips copywriting and discovery, not quality.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section tight">
    <h2 class="sr-only">Ongoing care</h2>
    <div class="wrap card care">
      <div class="care-grid">
        <div>
          <p class="kicker">Most clients choose this</p>
          <h3>Care plan — $45/month</h3>
          <p>
            The going rate for a website care plan is $95–195 a month — and most
            of those don't spell out what you get. Mine is $45, hosting included,
            and the scope is in writing, right here.
          </p>
        </div>
        <ul>
          <li><b>Hosting included</b> — fast, with SSL</li>
          <li><b>Two batches of content &amp; photo edits a month</b> — just email them in</li>
          <li><b>Two-business-day turnaround</b> on edits; broken-site fixes jump the queue</li>
          <li>Uptime monitoring with real alerting</li>
          <li>Backups you can download anytime + security updates</li>
          <li>Domain renewals handled (registration fees billed at cost)</li>
          <li>New pages or features quoted separately as small flat jobs</li>
          <li>Cancel anytime — you keep the site, the code, and a copy of everything</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="kicker">The math</p>
      <h2>Three years, side by side.</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-2">
        <div class="card math">
          <h3>Typical agency deal</h3>
          <p class="big">$7,600+</p>
          <p>$6,000 build + $45/month platform fee, forever — and that $45 buys
          hosting rent only, no updates. You can't edit your own site, and if you
          stop paying, it disappears. (This is a real local example; care plans
          that include actual updates run $95–195/month around here.)</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card math ours">
          <h3>My equivalent</h3>
          <p class="big">$4,520</p>
          <p>$2,900 build + $45/month care — hosting included, plus the monthly
          updates, monitoring, and backups spelled out above. Less than half the
          going monthly rate, and you own the site the whole time.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="kicker">How it works</p>
      <h2>Four steps, no meetings required (unless you want one).</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-2">
        <div class="card"><h3>1 · Email me</h3><p>Tell me what you do and what you have today (or don't have). I'll look at it and reply with a straight assessment.</p></div>
        <div class="card"><h3>2 · Flat quote</h3><p>One number for the whole build. If I find problems with your current site, you get the defect list either way.</p></div>
        <div class="card"><h3>3 · Build &amp; review</h3><p>You get a private preview link and two full revision rounds — most sites only need one. Tested on real phones, not just a desktop.</p></div>
        <div class="card"><h3>4 · Handover</h3><p>Site goes live on your domain. You own everything and get a plain-English guide to updating your content.</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="kicker">No surprises</p>
      <h2>The fine print, in plain English.</h2>
      <p class="lead">Most builds launch in two to four weeks.</p>
      <div class="grid grid-2">
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Paying</h3>
          <p>50% deposit to start, the balance when your site goes live — after
          you've seen it working on the preview link. The flat quote is the
          price; there are no surprise line items. If we part ways mid-build,
          you pay only for work already done.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Revisions</h3>
          <p>Two full revision rounds are included in every build. After that,
          changes are quoted as small flat jobs — there's no open-ended hourly
          meter, in either direction.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>What's included — and not</h3>
          <p>I'll shape and polish the words and photos you give me. Copywriting
          from scratch and professional photography aren't included — bring your
          own or I'll source licensed stock at cost. Extra pages beyond your
          package: $175 each, flat.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Handover &amp; warranty</h3>
          <p>Every build ends with a written handover: the code repository
          transferred to your name, the domain in your registrar account, and a
          plain-English guide any developer could follow. Anything broken in the
          first 30 days after launch, I fix free — care plan or not.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section tight">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="kicker">Beyond brochure sites</p>
      <h2>Need more than pages and a contact form?</h2>
      <p class="lead">
        Members-only areas, interactive maps, event systems, publishing
        workflows — that's the statewide club platform on my
        <a href="/work">Work page</a>, which I designed, built, and still
        operate. Projects like that don't fit a package, and I won't pretend
        they do: email me what you're trying to run and I'll write you a custom
        proposal.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CTABand heading="Got an agency quote sitting in your inbox?" sub="Forward it to me. I'll tell you what I'd charge for the same thing — usually about half." />
</Base>

<style>
  .price ul { padding-left: 1.2rem; color: var(--ink-soft); min-height: 8.5rem; }
  .price li { margin-bottom: 0.4rem; }
  .band {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.7rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin-bottom: 0.2rem;
  }
  .band span { font-size: 0.9rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--ink-soft); }
  .compare {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--warm);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-top: 0;
  }
  .fit { font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--ink-soft); margin: 0; }
  .featured { border-color: var(--accent); border-width: 2px; }
  .care { border-color: var(--warm); border-width: 2px; }
  .care-grid { display: grid; gap: 1.5rem; }
  @media (min-width: 760px) { .care-grid { grid-template-columns: 2fr 3fr; } }
  .care ul { padding-left: 1.2rem; color: var(--ink-soft); margin: 0; }
  .care li { margin-bottom: 0.45rem; }
  .math .big {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 2.4rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    margin: 0.2rem 0 0.5rem;
  }
  .math.ours { border-color: var(--accent); border-width: 2px; }
  .math.ours .big { color: var(--accent); }
</style>
